nl.tue.geometrycore.datastructures.doublylinkedlist

Class DoublyLinkedList<TItem extends DoublyLinkedListItem<TItem>>

  • java.lang.Object
    • nl.tue.geometrycore.datastructures.doublylinkedlist.DoublyLinkedList<TItem>
  • Type Parameters:
    TItem - class of items that are contained in the list
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Iterable<TItem>

    public class DoublyLinkedList<TItem extends DoublyLinkedListItem<TItem>>
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Iterable<TItem>
    A true doubly linked list. Note that it requires the stored objects to inherit from DoublyLinkedListItem. These objects can be stored in at most one list at a time. Calling methods on a list with objects from another list may result incorrect behavior.

      • clear

        public void clear()
        Empties the list. Note that it clears all the previous and next pointers stored with the elements, and ensures that they are no longer indicating to be part of a list. Thus this takes linear time.
